# Copy to `.env` in the repo root and fill in. Start the API with: npm run build && npm start
#
# --- Local Postgres (docker compose) ---
# Start the DB before `npm start` when the API uses Prisma: `docker compose up -d` or `.\scripts\db-up.ps1`.
# Matches docker-compose.yml: user relay, password relay, database relay_dev (host port 5433 → container 5432).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://relay:relay@localhost:5433/relay_dev
# Prisma 7 uses this URL with `@prisma/adapter-pg` in `src/lib/db.ts` (backfill scripts import the same client).
#
# --- Supabase (cloud Postgres + Auth) — MIG-01 ---
# Create **two** projects in the Supabase dashboard: **staging** and **production**. Each has its own
# project ref (subdomain of *.supabase.co) and API keys under Settings → API. Do not commit real keys.
# Replace YOUR_STAGING_REF / YOUR_PRODUCTION_REF with each project’s ref when wiring a host or local `.env`.
#
# HTTP API + Auth (same values exposed to the browser use NEXT_PUBLIC_* in web/.env.example).
# SUPABASE_STAGING_URL=https://YOUR_STAGING_REF.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_STAGING_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_PRODUCTION_URL=https://YOUR_PRODUCTION_REF.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_PRODUCTION_ANON_KEY=
#
# --- Relay session cookies (GR-T0-1) — API sets HttpOnly `relay_session` + companion `relay_signed_in` on auth responses.
# RELAY_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.relayapp.me
#   Production: leading dot shares cookies across subdomains (e.g. app + api). Omit for host-only cookies (typical localhost).
# RELAY_COOKIE_SECURE=1
#   When 1, Set-Cookie includes Secure. When 0, omits Secure (useful for plain HTTP local dev). Default: Secure in production only.
# RELAY_SESSION_TTL_SECONDS=86400
#   Max-Age for session cookies in seconds (default 86400 = 24h, aligned with Prisma Session TTL).
# RELAY_COOKIE_SESSION_DUAL_WRITE=1
#   When 1 (default), JSON auth responses still include `token` alongside Set-Cookie. Set 0 to omit token from JSON (cookie-only).
#
# MIG-11 — Relay API validates Supabase Auth JWTs on `POST /api/v1/auth/supabase/sync`.
# MT-033 — same JWT + `SUPABASE_*` used by `POST /api/v1/auth/supabase/relay-session` (opaque Relay patron session).
# Set these to the **same** Supabase project as `DATABASE_URL` for that environment (staging vs prod).
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_REF.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# Same project as DATABASE_URL — backfill scripts + src/lib/supabase-admin.ts
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# Server-only (never send to the client or check into git). Used for admin Auth APIs / migrations if needed.
# SUPABASE_STAGING_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# SUPABASE_PRODUCTION_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# MIG-12 — `npm run backfill:supabase-user-ids` — same Supabase project as DATABASE_URL / SUPABASE_URL.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# When Prisma targets Supabase Postgres instead of local Docker, set DATABASE_URL to the pooler connection
# string for **one** environment at a time (staging deploy vs prod deploy). Password and host come from
# Supabase Settings → Database. Pooler vs direct, SSL, CI: `docs/database/operations-and-security.md` § Supabase (`DATABASE_URL`).
# Example shape only (not a real host) — use the **Transaction pooler** URI from Supabase “Connect”:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.YOUR_STAGING_REF:YOUR_DB_PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
#
# **Single source of truth:** Prisma and `src/lib/db.ts` read only `DATABASE_URL` (no separate STAGING_DATABASE_URL).
# — **Cloud dev:** point `DATABASE_URL` at the **staging** Supabase project’s pooler (safe to iterate on).
# — **Production host:** set `DATABASE_URL` to the **production** project’s pooler. Optionally keep the prod URI
# in your secrets manager or a private note — not required as a second env var in this repo.
#
# Optional: store patron identity in Postgres (DbIdentityStore) instead of identity.json. Default off.
# See docs/database/staging-identity-verification.md for staging checks.
# RELAY_DB_STORE_IDENTITY=1
#
# Optional (MT-007): reserved Relay `creator_id` / Tenant.relay_creator_id for account-first email signup
# before joining a creator audience. Default __relay_platform. Change only if it collides with a real id.
# RELAY_PLATFORM_CREATOR_ID=__relay_platform
#
# Optional (MT-010): mutating creator routes — require X-Relay-Creator-Secret matching this value.
# When set (or RELAY_ENFORCE_CREATOR_TENANT=1), Postgres must have a Tenant row for the creator_id.
# T-5.1: the same `assertCreatorRelayMutationAllowed` gate runs on POST /api/v1/relay/posts and
# POST /api/v1/relay/upload/init|commit after Tier 1.1 `requireAccountMatchesCreator` (body creator_id
# must match Account.primaryRelayCreatorId, or 403).
# RELAY_CREATOR_ROUTE_SECRET=
# RELAY_ENFORCE_CREATOR_TENANT=0
#
# Optional (MT-011): Creator Patreon OAuth — HMAC secret for signed `state` from
# POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/creator/prepare (min 16 characters). Required when issuing state.
# RELAY_PATREON_OAUTH_STATE_SECRET=
#
# Extension browser consent — HMAC secret for one-time `consent_code` from
# POST /api/v1/auth/extension/consent/start (min 16 characters). Required for extension handshake.
# RELAY_EXTENSION_CONSENT_SECRET=
#
# Comma-separated extension origins permitted to hit /api/v1/auth/extension/*
# Get the production extension ID from chrome.google.com/webstore/devconsole after publishing
# Format: chrome-extension://<id>,moz-extension://<id>
# RELAY_EXTENSION_ORIGINS=chrome-extension://abcdefghijklmnop,moz-extension://abcdefghijklmnop
#
# Optional (MT-011): require Bearer session + signed `state` on POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/exchange.
# Operator bypass: set RELAY_CREATOR_ROUTE_SECRET and send X-Relay-Creator-Secret with the same value.
# RELAY_ENFORCE_CREATOR_OAUTH_BIND=0
#
# Optional (dev): Pipeline parity API — GET /api/dev/pipeline-parity/* requires this secret in header
# X-Relay-Pipeline-Parity-Secret. Used by web /dev/pipeline-parity and scripts/pipeline-parity-check.mjs.
# RELAY_PIPELINE_PARITY_SECRET=
#
# Optional: patron entitlement snapshot TTL after Patreon patron OAuth (milliseconds). Default 21600000 (6h).
# See src/identity/patron-entitlement-snapshot.ts (MIG-40).
# RELAY_PATRON_ENTITLEMENT_STALE_AFTER_MS=21600000
#
# Optional (PE-H): background stale entitlement refresh — interval in ms (minimum 60000). When set, the API
# process periodically re-fetches Patreon identity for snapshots past staleAfter using PatronOAuthCredential.
# RELAY_PATRON_ENTITLEMENT_REFRESH_MS=300000
# Optional: max rows per cycle (default 20).
# RELAY_PATRON_ENTITLEMENT_REFRESH_BATCH=20
#
# Patron Patreon-link gate (PE-A policy, 2026-04-20):
# Block POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/patron/link with 403 EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED when the linked Supabase account
# email is unconfirmed. Native-only accounts (no supabaseUserId) skip the check. Default 1 (enforced).
# Requires SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY pointing at the same project as DATABASE_URL.
RELAY_PATREON_LINK_REQUIRE_VERIFIED_EMAIL=1
#
# Legacy anonymous patron OAuth (POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/patron/exchange) is hard-deprecated. The route
# now refuses to create a brand-new Patreon-only account (returns 403 RELAY_ACCOUNT_REQUIRED). Set this to
# 1 ONLY for emergency rollback — Patreon links should always come from a signed-in, email-verified Account.
# RELAY_PATREON_PATRON_ALLOW_LEGACY_EXCHANGE=0
#
# Optional: canonical ingest + Patreon sync state in Postgres (see docs/database/staging-canonical-verification.md).
# Default off — uses .relay-data JSON files. Requires DATABASE_URL and `npm run db:migrate` (or migrate deploy).
# RELAY_DB_STORE_CANONICAL=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_WATERMARK=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_SYNC_HEALTH=1
#
# Optional: M4 curation JSON → Postgres (requires migrate + backfill:* scripts before enabling).
# RELAY_DB_STORE_OVERRIDES=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_COLLECTIONS=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_SAVED_FILTERS=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_LAYOUT=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_DLQ=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_EVENTS=1
#
# Optional: M6 analytics — Postgres (`DbAnalyticsStore`) instead of analytics.json. Default off (file store).
# Before setting RELAY_DB_STORE_ANALYTICS=1: valid DATABASE_URL; apply analytics migration
# (`npx prisma migrate deploy` on that environment); run `npm run backfill:analytics`; then enable and restart.
# See docs/database/README.md (Enabling Postgres-backed analytics).
# RELAY_DB_STORE_ANALYTICS=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_PATRON_ENGAGEMENT=1
#
# Optional: M8 Part 2 backend — clone / payments / migrations / deploys JSON → Postgres. Default off.
# Before enabling any flag: `npx prisma migrate deploy`; `npm run backfill:part2`; then enable only the
# stores you need and restart. Flags are independent (clone vs payments vs migration vs deploy).
# See docs/database/README.md (Enabling Postgres-backed Part 2 stores).
# RELAY_DB_STORE_CLONE=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_PAYMENTS=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_MIGRATION=1
# RELAY_DB_STORE_DEPLOY=1
#
# Optional: creator ingest OAuth tokens in Postgres (`DbPatreonTokenStore`) instead of
# `patreon_credentials.json`. Default off. Requires `DATABASE_URL`, `npx prisma migrate deploy`,
# and `prisma` passed from `main.ts` (same as other RELAY_DB_STORE_* flags). Prefer enabling
# after `RELAY_DB_STORE_IDENTITY=1` or re-run creator OAuth so `OAuthCredential` rows exist.
# RELAY_DB_STORE_CREATOR_OAUTH=1
#
# --- Cloudflare R2 (object storage, S3-compatible API) — MIG-30 ---
# Create an R2 bucket and an **R2 API token** (S3 credentials) in the Cloudflare dashboard.
# Store real values only in your host secrets manager — not in git.
# Default S3 endpoint: https://<R2_ACCOUNT_ID>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
# R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_BUCKET=
# Optional: override the endpoint (e.g. custom domain or non-default layout).
# R2_ENDPOINT=
# Optional: AWS SDK region label for SigV4 (R2 uses "auto").
# R2_REGION=auto
# Verify connectivity: npm run r2:smoke (uploads then deletes relay-smoke/*.txt)
#
# --- Relay native uploads (ADR 002, T-3.1 / T-3.2) — presigned PUT to R2 + commit in API ---
# Server mints a short-lived S3 presigned URL; the client PUTs the body directly to R2.
# Not all vars are read by the app until upload routes land; they document the contract.
# See: docs/architecture/adr/002-r2-creator-uploads-presigned-vs-server.md
# Presigned URL lifetime (seconds) when T-3.2 implements @aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner (typical: 5–15 min).
# R2_PRESIGN_EXPIRES_SEC=900

# Deferred R2 deletes (e.g. Discord staging removed from Library — DB row dropped first, object purged by worker).
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_SWEEP_MS — poll interval; empty = 1 hour, 0 = disable sweeper.
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_DELAY_MS — added to enqueue time before R2 delete (0 = eligible immediately). E.g. 2592000000 ≈ 30d.
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_BATCH — max queue rows per tick (default 25).
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_SWEEP_MS=3600000
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_DELAY_MS=0
# RELAY_MEDIA_STORAGE_PURGE_BATCH=25
# Reject init/commit if declared or observed object size exceeds this (bytes). Example: 500 MiB
# RELAY_UPLOAD_MAX_BYTES=524288000
# Comma-separated allowed MIME *prefix* checks (e.g. video,audio,image  →  video/*, audio/*, image/* in code, or set explicit subtypes).
# Optional; if unset, the app may use a built-in v1 list.
# RELAY_UPLOAD_ALLOWED_MIME_PREFIXES=video/,audio/,image/
#
# --- Discord channel capture (internal HMAC route, Phase 1) ---
# Bridge bot POSTs JSON to /api/v1/internal/discord/ingest with raw-body HMAC:
#   X-Relay-Discord-Signature: sha256=<hex>   where hex = HMAC-SHA256(RELAY_DISCORD_INGEST_HMAC_SECRET, rawBody)
# Generate secret: openssl rand -hex 32
# RELAY_DISCORD_INGEST_HMAC_SECRET=
# Optional: Discord bot token (same as bridge) so the API can download attachment URLs with Authorization: Bot …
# RELAY_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
#
# --- Discord bridge process (separate Node app) ---
# Loads `discord-bot/.env` then this root `.env`. Token: DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN or RELAY_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN above.
# Also required for slash registration: DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID (Developer Portal → Application ID).
# Optional: DISCORD_GUILD_ID, RELAY_API_URL (default http://127.0.0.1:8787). See discord-bot/README.md.
#
# These are your *OAuth application* credentials (one per Patreon app). They are NOT
# the creator’s access/refresh tokens — those are obtained only after a user completes
# OAuth and are stored encrypted (see web/.env.example + /patreon/connect flow).

# Required: Patreon OAuth app (Client ID / Client Secret from developer portal).
PATREON_CLIENT_ID=
PATREON_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Required: 32-byte key, base64 — used to encrypt stored Patreon access/refresh tokens.
# Example: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
RELAY_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Optional: override token endpoint (default: https://www.patreon.com/api/oauth2/token)
# PATREON_TOKEN_URL=

# Optional: sync watermark storage (default: .relay-data/patreon_sync_watermarks.json)
# RELAY_PATREON_SYNC_WATERMARK_PATH=

# --- Unattended incremental sync / fallback cadence (webhook safety net, T-008) ---
# Same interval worker as T-007: scheduled pulls that **complement** Patreon webhooks (T-006) when events
# are missed or delayed. Dedupe is via watermarks + per-creator serialization with webhook-triggered scrapes.
# Enable either: RELAY_AUTOSYNC_ENABLED=1 OR set RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_MS (≥ 10000).
# When 1/true/yes, runs periodic watermark-aware `scrapeOrSync` for every creator in the credential store.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_ENABLED=1
# Preferred interval knob (ms, min 10000). Also enables the worker without RELAY_AUTOSYNC_ENABLED.
# RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_MS=900000
# When RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_MS is set: run first cycle on boot (default 0/false).
# RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_RUN_ON_START=0
# Aliases for RELAY_AUTOSYNC_MAX_POST_PAGES / RELAY_AUTOSYNC_PROBE_SKIP (see below).
# RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_MAX_POST_PAGES=20
# RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_PROBE_SKIP=1
# Interval between cycles (ms). Minimum 60s enforced. Default 900000 (15 minutes).
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_INTERVAL_MS=900000
# Parallel creators per cycle (each creator still serializes webhook + autosync via PatreonSyncService). Default 2.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_CONCURRENCY=2
# Cap creators per cycle (0 = no cap). Default 0.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_MAX_CREATORS_PER_CYCLE=0
# Passed to scrape post pagination. Default 20 (max 100).
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_MAX_POST_PAGES=20
# When 1, skip creators whose stored OAuth health is refresh_failed. Default 0.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_SKIP_UNHEALTHY=0
# When 1 (default), call sync-state probe before scrape and skip if watermark exists and upstream shows no newer posts.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_PROBE_SKIP=1
# When 1, do not run a cycle immediately on process start; wait RELAY_AUTOSYNC_INITIAL_DELAY_MS then run on interval.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_SKIP_INITIAL_RUN=0
# Used only when RELAY_AUTOSYNC_SKIP_INITIAL_RUN=1. Default 60000 (1 minute).
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_INITIAL_DELAY_MS=60000
#
# Optional: add random 0..N ms to each scheduled cycle spacing (reduces lockstep with other timers).
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_INTERVAL_JITTER_MS=0
# Alias: RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_AUTOSYNC_JITTER_MS
#
# Optional: after any cycle with ≥1 creator failure, space the next run with exponential delay (capped).
# Resets to base interval after a fully successful cycle. Alias: RELAY_PATREON_INCREMENTAL_FALLBACK_BACKOFF
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_FAILURE_BACKOFF=0
# Cap on interval multiplier (default 8). Example: base 15m → up to 120m after repeated failures.
# RELAY_AUTOSYNC_FAILURE_BACKOFF_MAX_MULTIPLIER=8
#
# One-shot (no HTTP server): npm run build && npm run autosync:once

# Optional: last Patreon scrape / member sync health JSON (default: .relay-data/patreon_sync_health.json)
# RELAY_PATREON_SYNC_HEALTH_PATH=

# Optional: Patreon campaign avatar, banner URLs, patron_count snapshot (default: .relay-data/creator_campaign_display.json)
# RELAY_CREATOR_CAMPAIGN_DISPLAY_PATH=

# Production: HTTPS origin of this API for Patreon webhook registration (no trailing slash).
# OAuth exchange and POST /api/v1/patreon/webhooks/register use this to build
# /api/v1/webhooks/patreon/platform/:token. Alias: PUBLIC_WEBHOOK_BASE_URL.
# Runbook: docs/patreon-webhooks-operations.md
# RELAY_PUBLIC_WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# Optional: public /visitor gallery hero title (GET /api/v1/gallery/facets?visitor=true → visitor_hero.relay_display_name).
# Use the same value as web NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAY_CREATOR_DISPLAY_NAME so the Library and public gallery match.
# RELAY_CREATOR_DISPLAY_NAME=

# API listen port (default 8787 — matches web/lib/relay-api.ts default)
# PORT=8787

# Visitor gallery: allow ?dev_sim_patron=true&simulate_tier_ids=… to simulate patron tier access (redaction only).
# Never enable in production. Requires web NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAY_VISITOR_DEV_TOOLS to expose the UI toggle.
# RELAY_DEV_VISITOR_TIER_SIM=true

# When 1, GET /api/v1/export/media/:creator_id/:media_id/content requires a valid patron
# Bearer session (or public-tier post). Default off so the Library can load thumbnails without OAuth.
# RELAY_EXPORT_REQUIRE_TIER_ACCESS=1

# Optional: export download retries (defaults: 3 attempts, 500ms base backoff, 60s timeout per attempt)
# RELAY_EXPORT_MAX_ATTEMPTS=3
# RELAY_EXPORT_BASE_DELAY_MS=500
# RELAY_EXPORT_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS=60000

# --- Ingest + DLQ health gates (Workstream B, T-009) — GET /api/v1/health/ingest ---
# In-process counters since process start; optional alerts when thresholds are exceeded.
# Minimum completed batches before ratio alerts apply (default 20).
# RELAY_INGEST_HEALTH_MIN_BATCHES_FOR_ALERTS=20
# Alert if IngestRetryQueue pending jobs exceed this (default 50).
# RELAY_INGEST_ALERT_MAX_PENDING_RETRIES=50
# Alert if persistent DLQ row count exceeds this (0 = disabled).
# RELAY_INGEST_ALERT_MAX_DLQ_RECORDS=0
# Alert if dlq_appends / batches_completed exceeds this after min batches (0 = disabled). Example: 0.01 = 1%.
# RELAY_INGEST_ALERT_MAX_DLQ_PER_BATCH=0
# Alert if idempotent_skips / (skips + rows_mutated) exceeds this — possible replay storm (default 0.999).
# RELAY_INGEST_ALERT_MAX_DUPLICATE_RATIO=0.999

# --- Part 1 A exit gates (T-010) — GET /api/v1/health/part1a ---
# Counters are since process boot (restart resets). Optional alerts when samples exceed thresholds.
# RELAY_PART1A_MIN_SAMPLES_FOR_ALERTS=20
# Alert if creator POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/exchange completion falls below this (0–1). Default 0.95.
# RELAY_PART1A_ALERT_CREATOR_OAUTH_MIN_COMPLETION=0.95
# Alert if token refresh failure ratio exceeds this (failures / (success+failures)). Default 0.01 (1%).
# RELAY_PART1A_ALERT_TOKEN_REFRESH_MAX_FAILURE_RATIO=0.01

# --- Analytics insight jobs (Workstream E, T-012) — GET /api/v1/health/analytics ---
# Counters for POST /api/v1/analytics/generate since process boot (restart resets).
# RELAY_INSIGHT_JOB_ALERT_MIN_SAMPLES=50
# Alert when failure_ratio (failures / (successes+failures)) exceeds this after min samples. Default 0.01 (1%).
# RELAY_INSIGHT_JOB_ALERT_MAX_FAILURE_RATIO=0.01

# --- Redis (Phase P1 — BullMQ job backend) ---
# Required when RELAY_JOB_BACKEND=bullmq (see docs/pilot-build-plan.md Phase P1). Used by workers only.
# Local: `docker run -p 6379:6379 redis:7-alpine` then point REDIS_URL at localhost.
# Managed Redis often uses TLS (`rediss://`) and a non-default port.
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
# Example (password / ACL user): redis://default:YOUR_PASSWORD@your-host:6379/0
# Example (TLS): rediss://default:YOUR_PASSWORD@your-host:6380/0
#
# Optional integration test: run Redis locally, then:
#   set SKIP_REDIS_IT=0 and REDIS_URL to the same value (Windows PowerShell):
#   $env:SKIP_REDIS_IT='0'; $env:REDIS_URL='redis://localhost:6379'; npm test -- tests/redis-connection.test.ts

# --- Export retrieval SLO (Workstream C, T-013) — GET /api/v1/health/export ---
# Counters since process boot. Optional alerts on GET content failure ratio vs ~99.9% target.
# RELAY_EXPORT_HEALTH_MIN_SAMPLES=30
# Alert when (failures / (successes+failures)) exceeds this after min samples. Default 0.001 (0.1%).
# RELAY_EXPORT_HEALTH_MAX_CONTENT_FAILURE_RATIO=0.001
# Checksum sampling: POST /api/v1/export/integrity-sample { "creator_id", "limit" } (cap 50).

# --- Not used as env vars in this codebase ---
# "Client API Version" (e.g. v2): choose in the Patreon portal only; pass ?api_version=2
# on Patreon resource requests when you implement the Patreon fetch/sync layer.
#
# "Creator's Access Token" / "Creator's Refresh Token" from the portal: do not paste
# into .env. After OAuth, this app stores encrypted tokens via POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/exchange
# in RELAY_CREDENTIAL_STORE_PATH (default .relay-data/patreon_credentials.json).
#
# How to test OAuth end-to-end (use ONE browser origin; see docs/qa/DEV_LOCAL_ORIGIN.md — recommend 127.0.0.1):
# 1. Register redirect http://127.0.0.1:3000/patreon/callback (or your chosen URL) in Patreon.
# 2. Root .env: PATREON_CLIENT_ID, PATREON_CLIENT_SECRET, RELAY_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY → npm run build && npm start
# 3. web/.env.local: NEXT_PUBLIC_* from web/.env.example → cd web && npm run dev
# 4. Open http://127.0.0.1:3000/patreon/connect → Continue to Patreon → approve → callback exchanges code.
#    Patron login (syncs tier_ids + session): http://127.0.0.1:3000/patreon/patron/connect — add
#    redirect http://127.0.0.1:3000/patreon/patron/callback in Patreon; API: POST /api/v1/auth/patreon/patron/exchange
# 5. Pull posts into Relay: POST /api/v1/patreon/scrape with { "creator_id": "...", "dry_run": true } first.
# Automated test (no real Patreon): npm test — tests/workstream-a.patreon-oauth.happy-path.test.ts mocks the token URL.
